  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nAt the moment, when running Forge tests against a fork of a running network (e.g. Ethereum mainnet), when doing `blockhash(someBlockNumber)`, the result is 0.\r\nThe desired behavior would be as in the Ethereum mainnet EVM environment, having access to the last 256 blocks.\r\nThis is especially important for use cases involving the verification of storage proofs against historic block hashes.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
